article.headline: CS Northridge 78, Cleveland St. 68
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Calvin Chitwood scored 22 points Wednesday night to lead Cal State Northridge to a 78-68 win over Cleveland State, snapping the Vikings' three-game winning streak. With Cleveland State leading 44-42 midway through the second half, Dean Tresvant made a 3-pointer to spark a 25-13 run that gave the Matadors a 67-57 lead with 4:02 remaining. Tremaine Townsend scored 16 points and had 15 rebounds for the Matadors (4-0). Josh Jenkins scored 14 and Jonathan Heard added 10. Cedric Jackson scored 24 points for Cleveland State (4-3), which let a 31-29 halftime lead slip away and shot 40.6 percent (26 of 64) for the game. Cal State Northridge shot 43.1 percent (25 of 58).
